Package xxl.core.pipes.sources

Interface Summary
Source<O> Our framework for query processing is based on dataflow graphs, therefore it consists of three fundamental types of components: sources, operators, and sinks.
SourceMetaDataManagement  
SourceMetaDataManagement.ContainsSourceMetaDataDependencies  
 

Class Summary
AbstractSource<O> Superclass for each kind of initial sources in a query graph.
AbstractSource.SourceMetaDataDependenciesContainer Container for the meta data dependencies of an AbstractSource.
AbstractTemporalSource<O> Superclass for sources that transfer instances of TemporalObject, i.e., the transferred elements consist of a value and a time interval.
AbstractTimeStampSource<O,O2 extends TimeStampedObject<O>> Superclass for sources that transfer TimeStampedObjects, i.e., the transferred elements consist of a value and a time stamp.
CursorSource<T> Source component in a query graph that permits access to an iterator.
Enumerator Source component in a query graph that delivers an ascending or descending sequence of integer objects.
Permutator<T>  
RandomNumber<T extends Number> Source component in a query graph that produces a (finite or infinite) stream of randomly distributed elements.
SyncTimeStampSource<O>  
SyncTimeStampSource.RecallIterator  
TimeStampCursorSource<O>  
 

Exception Summary
SourceIsClosedException This exception is thrown to indicate that a source has already stopped transfering elements, because it has received a close call.
